)

CREATE TABLE "model_list" ( 
	"ModelId" INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, 
	"Maker" INTEGER, 
	"Model" TEXT UNIQUE,
	FOREIGN KEY (Maker) REFERENCES car_makers (Id)

)

CREATE TABLE "car_names" (

	"Model" TEXT,

	FOREIGN KEY (Model) REFERENCES model_list (Model)
)

	"Id" INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, 
	"MPG" TEXT, 
	"Cylinders" INTEGER, 
	"Edispl" REAL, 
	"Horsepower" TEXT, 
	"Weight" INTEGER, 
	"Accelerate" REAL, 
	"Year" INTEGER,
	FOREIGN KEY (Id) REFERENCES car_names (MakeId)
)

SELECT

)

	"Year" INTEGER,
	FOREIGN KEY (Id) REFERENCES car_names (MakeId)

/* Given the following database schema: */
CREATE TABLE "TV_Channel" (
"id" text,
"series_name" text,
"Country" text,
"Language" text,
"Content" text,
"Pixel_aspect_ratio_PAR" text,
"Hight_definition_TV" text,
"Pay_per_view_PPV" text,
"Package_Option" text,
PRIMARY KEY ("id")
)

"id" real,
"Episode" text,
"Air_Date" text,
"Rating" text,
"Share" real,
"18_49_Rating_Share" text,

"id" real,

"Channel" text,
PRIMARY KEY ("id"),

)

/* Answer the following: List the title of all  Cartoons showed on TV Channel with series name "Sky Radio". */
SELECT
questions.response: T2.Title FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN Cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T1.series_name = "Sky Radio";
